Name: Adelaide
Description:
The Division of Adelaide consists of:

  • Adelaide City Council,
  • City of Prospect,
  • Corporation of the Town of Walkerville,
  • part of the City of Burnside,
  • part of the City of Charles Sturt,
  • part of the City of Port Adelaide Enfield,
  • part of the City of Unley, and
  • part of the City of West Torrens
ProductsAndIndustry: Adelaide central business district, Adelaide Oval, brewery, hospitals, light industry, markets, military barracks, South Australia Parliament, Government House and universities.
NameDerivation: Named after the city covered by the electoral division. The city was named by King William IV after his Consort, Queen Adelaide.
